This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence labeling and information extraction from unstructured natural language data. Additionally, the paper focuses on the clinical domain, which is a specific area of interest within the larger field of natural language processing. 

The paper also involves the use of structured learning models with Recurrent Neural Networks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper proposes an approximate version of skip-chain CRF inference with RNN potentials, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves the detection of medical entities from text, which could be seen as a form of image recognition applied to natural language data.
